descript.abstract:
This dataset represents polygon coverage of coral reefs worldwide developed under the Millennium Coral Reef Mapping Project funded by NASA and IRD. The polygons are derived from the interpretation and classification of Landsat images. The Landsat images used are publicly available from http://oceancolor.gsfc.nasa.gov/cgi/landsat.pl
Coral reefs are described hierarchically following five levels of geomorphologic and geographic information (L1, L2, L3, L4, L5). The most detailed scheme (L5) includes approximately 800 classes.
The product also includes the most accurate shoreline product to date, obtained after interpretation from Landsat images, and since 2005, after correction of the Shuttle Radar Terrain Mission water-body product.

dataqual.logic:
This dataset was created through manual image interpretation of Landsat satellite imagery. For a detailed description of the mapping process, please refer to the following publication:
Andrefouet S, Muller-Karger FE, Robinson JA, Kranenburg CJ, Torres-Pulliza D, Spraggins SA, Murch B, "Global assessment of modern coral reef extent and diversity for regional science and management applications: a view from space", Proceedings of 10th International Coral Reef Symposium (ICRS '04), 2006 (1732:1745).
